{
  "title": "Abortive Infection Mechanisms and Prophage Sequences Significantly Influence the Genetic Makeup of Emerging Lytic Lactococcal Phages",
  "summary": "The study characterizes the morphology of wild-type lactococcal phage ul36 and its Abi-resistant mutants, all belonging to the P335 group. Wild-type ul36 has an isometric capsid, a noncontractile tail, and a two-disk baseplate. Mutants ul36.t1, ul36.t1k1, and ul36.k1t1 have a one-disk baseplate and slightly longer tails (120 ± 6.2 nm) compared to ul36 and ul36.k1 (99 ± 5 nm). The inducible prophage φsmq86 shares morphological features with these three mutants.",
